</section>
  <section class="section-summary" id="sect-00005">
<para id="para-00023">Databases and registries are potential sources of reliable, evidence-based interventions. Additional frames of reference include the WHO’s Essential Public Health Functions (EPHF) and the CDC’s 10 Essential Public Health Services (EPHS). Research ethics are fundamental principles that guide the design and implementation of research. Nurses must consider their role in protecting the population being researched and promoting equity in research to better serve their communities.</para>
</section>
